# TOKEN-SAVING & PERFORMANCE RULES
- Be extremely concise. Avoid conversational filler.
- DO NOT rewrite entire files. Only provide the specific snippets or functions that need changing.
- When suggesting changes, use the format: "In [filename], change [old code] to [new code]".
- DO NOT explain how React or Tailwind works unless I explicitly ask "Why?".
- Before reading a file, check if it's already in the context history to save tokens.
- Priority: Functionality first, then performance, then aesthetics.
- If a task is unclear, ask ONE clarifying question instead of guessing and wasting tokens.

# PROJECT CONTEXT
- This is a high-end creative studio website (Magic Pop Studio).
- Tech stack: React, Vite, Tailwind CSS, Framer Motion (motion/react).
- Keep the "Blob" animations and proximity effects intact unless told otherwise.